title: Double-perp lemma
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Let $$H$$ be a (possibly infinite-dimensional) vector space with a scalar product, $$U \subseteq H$$ a finite-dimensional subspace and $$V \subseteq H$$ a subspace with $$V^\perp = \{0\}.$$ Then
$$
(U^\perp \cap V)^\perp = U.
$$